{"title":"Giant Renews Faith In the Youth Market With Serious Kids Trail Bike","link":"https://bikerumor.com/giant-faith-kids-mountain/","date":1718294400000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-header-1536x1152.jpeg\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1152\" alt=\"Giant Faith header\" /></p>\n<p>We have Faith in the youth to carry on the traditions, stewardship, and love of riding bikes. Giant Bicycles is renewing that Faith with an all-new, updated youth mountain bike. It’s a renewal, as the Giant Faith isn’t a new line, but it’s reimagined for a new generation of kids who want to have fun and shred. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The Giant Faith is specifically for developing young riders. The new range features purpose-built (youth-friendly) suspension, updated geometry, and components for smaller, lighter bodies.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-graphics--scaled.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1920\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-graphics--scaled.jpeg\" alt=\"Giant Faith graphics\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-graphics--scaled.jpeg 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-graphics--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-graphics--1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-graphics--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-graphics--768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-graphics--2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /></a><figcaption>(All photos: Jordan Villella/Bikerumor)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>A Return of Faith </h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The new Faith range is the first of its kind from Giant. It’s a collection of high-performance, full-suspension trail bikes that are on par with adult mountain bikes. The difference is that they are specifically dialed for youth use and dimensions—right down to the dropper seatpost. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-headtube-scaled.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1920\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-headtube-scaled.jpeg\" alt=\"Giant Faith headtube\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-headtube-scaled.jpeg 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-headtube-297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-headtube-1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-headtube-120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-headtube-768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-headtube-2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The updated Giant Faith line starts with an aluminum frame with youth-specific geometry. The updated geometry expertly matches Giants’ all-new proprietary suspension setups, WheelSystems, and ergonomic touchpoints for smaller bodies. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The small bike packs a lot of cool tech, so let’s start at the base. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-headtube-welds--scaled.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1920\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-headtube-welds--scaled.jpeg\" alt=\"Giant Faith headtube welds\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-headtube-welds--scaled.jpeg 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-headtube-welds--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-headtube-welds--1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-headtube-welds--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-headtube-welds--768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-headtube-welds--2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Giant ALUXX SL Frameset</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Let’s start with the frame. The Faith’s canvas is a high-performance ALUXX SL aluminum frameset with youth-specific trail geometry. Weight is a big part of the picture here, and Giant wants to keep the Faith as slim and sleek as possible. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-routing--scaled.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1152\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-routing--1536x1152.jpeg\" alt=\"Giant Faith routing\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-routing--1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-routing--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-routing--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-routing--768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-routing--2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-welds--scaled.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1152\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-welds--1536x1152.jpeg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-welds--1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-welds--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-welds--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-welds--768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-welds--2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The frame boasts features like internal cable routing, dropper post compatibility, and a tapered headtube. Its construction looks very beefy and on par with some serious alloy trail bikes. The graphics are cool and understated, with a bit of skate style mixed in. Plus, there is lots of blank space for stickers, and if your kids are like mine… the more, the better. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-hubset--scaled.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1920\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-hubset--scaled.jpeg\" alt=\"Giant Faith hubset\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-hubset--scaled.jpeg 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-hubset--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-hubset--1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-hubset--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-hubset--768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-hubset--2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>TRA WheelSystems</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Next up is the wheelset, and that, too, is youth-focused. Giant’s new youth-specific TRA WheelSystems borrows essential tech from the adult TRA WheelSystem, including nice modern wide rims, performance-level hubs, and extra thought put into the longevity of the build. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-UDH--scaled.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1920\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-UDH--scaled.jpeg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-UDH--scaled.jpeg 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-UDH--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-UDH--1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-UDH--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-UDH--768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-UDH--2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The rims are slightly overbuilt, with 5mm rim walls that hopefully will keep these kiddos dent-free for a while. The rear wheel boasts a 72-tooth freehub, better than some adult mountain bikes. The hubs are easily serviceable, like most Giant TRA hubs, and should last. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-shock--scaled.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1920\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-shock--scaled.jpeg\" alt=\"Giant Faith shock\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-shock--scaled.jpeg 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-shock--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-shock--1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-shock--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-shock--768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-shock--2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Suspension Tuned for Young Riders</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>How a young rider sees the trail differs significantly from how a 6-foot-tall adult blasts through the single track. Their bikes should be able to tackle those unique demands and try not to hinder their riding growth. Giant feels the best way to overcome this is variable wheel sizes and suspension tuned specifically for kids. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-shock-mounting--scaled.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1152\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-shock-mounting--1536x1152.jpeg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-shock-mounting--1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-shock-mounting--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-shock-mounting--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-shock-mounting--768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-shock-mounting--2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-suspension-close-up--scaled.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1152\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-suspension-close-up--1536x1152.jpeg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-suspension-close-up--1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-suspension-close-up--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-suspension-close-up--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-suspension-close-up--768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-suspension-close-up--2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Giant Faith uses the Giant FlexPoint rear suspension system with a Crest FloTrac Lite shock. New Crest Lite suspension forks with FloTune Lite dampers help kids tackle technical terrain with more confidence and control.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-saddle--scaled.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1920\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-saddle--scaled.jpeg\" alt=\"Giant Faith saddle\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-saddle--scaled.jpeg 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-saddle--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-saddle--1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-saddle--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-saddle--768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-saddle--2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Two Distinct Giant Faith Models</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The new Giant Faith range includes two models. The Giant Faith features a new Giant TRA WheelSystem with a 27.5-inch front wheel and 26-inch rear. The wheels borrow vital features and technologies from race-proven adult TRA WheelSystems, including WideGuard technology, to improve rim strength and reduce the risk of flats. The smaller Faith 24 has 24-inch TRA wheels front and rear for lighter weight and easier handling.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-dropper--scaled.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1152\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-dropper--1536x1152.jpeg\" alt=\"Giant Faith dropper\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-dropper--1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-dropper--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-dropper--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-dropper--768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-dropper--2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-dropper-close-up--scaled.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1152\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-dropper-close-up--1536x1152.jpeg\" alt=\"Giant Faith dropper close up\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-dropper-close-up--1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-dropper-close-up--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-dropper-close-up--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-dropper-close-up--768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-dropper-close-up--2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-frame-rear--scaled.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1152\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-frame-rear--1536x1152.jpeg\" alt=\"Giant Faith frame rear\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-frame-rear--1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-frame-rear--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-frame-rear--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-frame-rear--768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-frame-rear--2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>All Faith models have youth-specific cranks, brake levers, and new Contact Switch AT Lite dropper seat posts. The Contact Switch AT Lite dropper has a lighter action and requires less force/weight to initiate the drop, making it much easier for kids to use. The grips and levers are also youth-focused, with a smaller diameter grip and easier-to-access levers.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-travel--scaled.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1920\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-travel--scaled.jpeg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-travel--scaled.jpeg 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-travel--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-travel--1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-travel--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-travel--768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-travel--2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Super Active FlexPoint Rear Suspension</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Both Faith models feature FlexPoint rear suspension systems with a Crest FloTrac Lite shock. This linkage-driven, single-pivot system creates consistent damping and spring performance throughout the travel. Like larger Giant bikes, it isolates the rear shock to provide small bump sensitivity through the entire wheel path. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-Nino-DH.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2305\" height=\"1729\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-Nino-DH.jpeg\" alt=\"Giant Faith Nino DH\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-Nino-DH.jpeg 2305w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-Nino-DH-297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-Nino-DH-1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-Nino-DH-120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-Nino-DH-768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-Nino-DH-2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /></a><figcaption>When you forget your helmet, you wear Dads… Photo: Jordan Villella</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Kids may or may not notice all the subtle nuances of the tech, but they can sure feel if it’s smooth. My son describes it as having a “magic carpet feel.” The above result is a smooth, active feel through the shock stroke with no harsh bottom-outs.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-fork-lowers--scaled.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1920\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-fork-lowers--scaled.jpeg\" alt=\"Giant Faith fork lowers\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-fork-lowers--scaled.jpeg 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-fork-lowers--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-fork-lowers--1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-fork-lowers--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-fork-lowers--768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-fork-lowers--2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Crest FloTrac Lite-Shock</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The Crest FloTrac Lite-Shock is designed and built in-house to complement Giant’s suspension platform kinematics for lightweight riders. It receives custom tuning for less force input and lightweight action.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-fork-top--scaled.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1920\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-fork-top--scaled.jpeg\" alt=\"Giant Faith fork top\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-fork-top--scaled.jpeg 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-fork-top--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-fork-top--1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-fork-top--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-fork-top--768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-fork-top--2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Paired with Giants Triple Flow Path technology that stabilizes the shock’s motion when active, Crest FloTrac Lite gives smaller riders increased traction and control while descending or climbing. The Crest TR Elite Lite and Crest SL FloTune Lite forks are custom-tuned for light riders. The design boasts low-friction action and the latest Giant FloTune Lite damper. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-rear-tire-clearance--scaled.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1920\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-rear-tire-clearance--scaled.jpeg\" alt=\"Giant Faith rear tire clearance\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-rear-tire-clearance--scaled.jpeg 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-rear-tire-clearance--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-rear-tire-clearance--1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-rear-tire-clearance--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-rear-tire-clearance--768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-rear-tire-clearance--2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>In addition, all Faith models feature Unified Suspension Setup, a guide displayed on the forks indicating optimal air pressure, and damper setting recommendations for both the rear shock and the fork based on rider weight. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-chain-guard-1-1-scaled.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1920\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-chain-guard-1-1-scaled.jpeg\" alt=\"Giant Faith chain guard\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-chain-guard-1-1-scaled.jpeg 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-chain-guard-1-1-297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-chain-guard-1-1-1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-chain-guard-1-1-120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-chain-guard-1-1-768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-chain-guard-1-1-2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>135mm or 130mm of Real Travel </h3>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>The Faith</strong> series has 135mm of rear Travel,  with a 140mm Crest SL FloTune Lite fork, which is explicitly tuned for riders weighing under 62kg. The <strong>Faith 24 </strong>series has 130mm of rear Travel and is paired with a 140mm Crest TR Elite Lite Fork, which is also explicitly tuned for riders weighing under 46kg.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-crankset--scaled.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1920\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-crankset--scaled.jpeg\" alt=\"Giant Faith crankset\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-crankset--scaled.jpeg 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-crankset--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-crankset--1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-crankset--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-crankset--768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-crankset--2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Spec’d to Climb and Descend </h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Going down the hills is fun, but going up is OK, too, if you have the correct gears. Either Faith model comes with Microshift Advent X G-Series-10-speed, an 11×48 cassette paired with a 30T front chain ring. The crankset is a short 155mm (or 140mm on the 24″ model), hoping to limit pedal strikes and foster a balance of cadence and power. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-mount-scaled.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1152\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-mount-1536x1152.jpeg\" alt=\"Giant Faith mount\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-mount-1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-mount-297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-mount-120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-mount-768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-mount-2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-shock-mounting--scaled.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1152\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-shock-mounting--1536x1152.jpeg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-shock-mounting--1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-shock-mounting--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-shock-mounting--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-shock-mounting--768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-shock-mounting--2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-grips--scaled.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1152\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-grips--1536x1152.jpeg\" alt=\"Giant Faith grips\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-grips--1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-grips--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-grips--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-grips--768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-grips--2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>There is no front derailleur, but there is a very beefy Giant chain guide. Paired with the Advent X G-Series derailleur equals zero dropped chains. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-tires-1-1-scaled.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1152\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-tires-1-1-1536x1152.jpeg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-tires-1-1-1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-tires-1-1-297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-tires-1-1-120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-tires-1-1-768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-tires-1-1-2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-tires--scaled.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1152\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-tires--1536x1152.jpeg\" alt=\"Giant Faith tires\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-tires--1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-tires--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-tires--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-tires--768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-tires--2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Tire-wise, the Faith gets serious, arriving with Maxxis Minion DHR II, 2.4, 60 TPI TLR. Paired with the Tektro hydraulic brakes with 180/160mm rotors, this bike should able to take on mountains!  </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-GEO-.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1030\" height=\"902\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-GEO-.png\" alt=\"Giant Faith GEO\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-GEO-.png 1030w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-GEO--297x260.png 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-GEO--120x105.png 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-GEO--768x673.png 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Giant Faith Geometry </h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-chain-guard--scaled.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1920\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-chain-guard--scaled.jpeg\" alt=\"Giant Faith chain guard\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-chain-guard--scaled.jpeg 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-chain-guard--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-chain-guard--1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-chain-guard--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-chain-guard--768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-chain-guard--2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2><strong>Giant Faith Full Spec’s</strong></h2>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Colors</strong>: Copper</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Frame</strong>: ALUXX SL-Grade Aluminum front and rear triangles, 12x148mm thru-axle, 135mm FlexPoint suspension</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Fork</strong>: Crest SL FloTune Lite, FloTune Lite Damper, 140mm</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Shock</strong>: Crest FloTrac Lite, 165/45mm, trunnion mount</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Handlebar</strong>: Giant Contact TR, 20mm rise, AL6061 aluminum, 740mm</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Grips</strong>: Giant small-hand</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Stem</strong>: Giant Contact, 8 degrees, 40mm</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Seatpost</strong>: Contact Switch AT Lite, 100mm</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Saddle</strong>: Giant Romero</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Pedals</strong>: Giant Pinner Lite</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Shifters</strong>: MicroSHIFT Advent X Trail trigger shifter SL-M9505-R (with nanowire)</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Rear Derailleur</strong>: Microshift Advent X RD-M6205AM</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Brakes</strong>: Tektro, 180mm/160mm</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Brake Levers</strong>: Tektro HD-J285</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Cassette</strong>: Microshift Advent X G-Series, 10-speed, 11×48</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Crankset</strong>: ProWheel Charm, 30t, 155mm</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Bottom Bracket</strong>: Press Fit</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Rims</strong>: Giant TRA WheelSystem, alloy, hollow rim wall construction, hookless, 30mm inner width, 40mm outer width, 21mm height, Wide Guard Technology.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Hubs</strong>: Front- Giant alloy, DBL, six-bolt. Rear – TRA 72t pawl driver, six-bolt</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Spokes</strong>: Sapim Laser</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Tires</strong>: Maxxis Minion DHR II, 26×2.4, 60 TPI, folding</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Extras</strong>: Giant 1x chain guide</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-Nino-dialing-in--scaled.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1920\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-Nino-dialing-in--scaled.jpeg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-Nino-dialing-in--scaled.jpeg 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-Nino-dialing-in--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-Nino-dialing-in--1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-Nino-dialing-in--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-Nino-dialing-in--768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Giant-Faith-Nino-dialing-in--2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>What Size Faith Does My Rider Need?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Giant gives some rough outlines of the size guidance. </p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Faith 24: </strong>5-9 years old and features a 64.1 cm (25.2 in) standover height—27 pounds with pedals.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Faith is</strong> 9-13 years old and has a 67.6 cm (26.6 in) standover height—29 pounds with pedals.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h3>Pricing and Availability</h3>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Faith $2,500</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Faith 24″ $2,600</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p><em>All Giant Faith models are available at Giant.com or your local Giant retailer, as we suggest dialing in the perfect size. </em></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Look for our first impressions shortly! </p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"http://www.giant-bicycles.com/faith-range\">www.giant-bicycles.com/faith-range</a></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/giant-faith-kids-mountain/\">Giant Renews Faith In the Youth Market With Serious Kids Trail Bike</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Jordan Villella","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"3484e89bb67c5c4a93f5e7cf3ff34a6e48489e11cd8c85d43b876e23fc360ee2","category":"Cycling"}